<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"isPasted"><strong>How to Make Scented =
Candles With Essential Oils or Fragrance Oil</strong></h2>



<p>If you want to add a scent to homemade candles, follow the recipe above =
and add the scent during Step 7. There are two main options for adding scen=
t to the candles:&nbsp;<strong>essential oils or fragrance oils.</strong></=
p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Essential oils or a blend of essential oils</strong>&nbsp;is th=
e most natural option. Essential oils&nbsp;<em>aren=E2=80=99t</em>&nbsp;as =
powerful as fragrance oils. I love lavender, eucalyptus, lemongrass, pepper=
mint, or grapefruit essential oil for a candle. I use about 60 drops of ess=
ential oil per candle.  <strong><a href=3D"https://livesimply.me/live-simpl=
y-podcast-essentials-oils/">Learn more about using essential oils</a></stro=
ng>.</li>



<li><strong>To make homemade candles smell stronger,&nbsp;<a href=3D"https:=
//www.candlescience.com/fragrance-oil/all-fragrance-oils/" target=3D"_blank=
" rel=3D"nofollow">fragrance oils</a>&nbsp;are the strongest scent option.<=
/strong>&nbsp;I can=E2=80=99t tell what goes into making fragrance oils jus=
t by reading the ingredient list, so if you go with this option you may wan=
t to call the company first and ask for a disclosure of ingredients. Use th=
e brand=E2=80=99s recommended dosage amount on the package when adding frag=
rance oils.</li>



<li><strong>Dried herbs, like crushed roses, lavender, or rosemary, may als=
o be used in a candle</strong>, with caution (keeping an eye on the candle =
when it=E2=80=99s burning), but they don=E2=80=99t provide much fragrance. =
I=E2=80=99ve also seen candle makers use coffee beans as well. </li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<div class=3D"wp-block-group"><div class=3D"wp-block-group__inner-container=
 is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><strong>How to Prevent Problems With DIY Can=
dles&nbsp;</strong></h2>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>It=E2=80=99s best to allow the candle to =E2=80=9Ccure=E2=80=9D=
 for 24 hours before use.</strong> Just let the candle rest before use, whi=
ch allows the wax time to fully harden. But if you want to burn it right aw=
ay, you=E2=80=99re welcome to do so. </li>



<li>Once the wax is solid, <strong>trim the wicks down to about 1 inch</str=
ong>.</li>



<li><strong>If there are any cracks or tunneling in the wax</strong>, melt =
a bit more wax and fill in the cracks with the wax. The candles are still u=
sable with tunneling or cracks in the wax; it=E2=80=99s just a cosmetic iss=
ue. </li>



<li><strong>To prevent the wax from tunneling the first time you burn the c=
andles</strong>, burn the candle long enough so there=E2=80=99s liquid acro=
ss entire the top before extinguishing.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
